---
import LegalLayout from "@/layouts/LegalLayout.astro";

export const prerender = true;

const sections = [
  { id: "summary", label: "Summary" },
  { id: "general", label: "General policy" },
  { id: "per-product", label: "Per-product rules" },
  { id: "agency", label: "Agency engagements" },
  { id: "how-to-request", label: "How to request a refund" },
  { id: "processing", label: "Processing time" },
  { id: "exceptions", label: "Exceptions" },
  { id: "disputes", label: "Disputes" },
];
---
<LegalLayout
  title="Refund Policy"
  description="ZafTech's refund rules for SaaS subscriptions, per-product terms, and agency engagements."
  effectiveDate="2026-04-24"
  lastUpdated="2026-04-24"
  sections={sections}
  summary="We want you paying for something that actually works for you. This policy lays out exactly when you can get your money back, by product, and how to request it."
>
  <h2 id="summary" data-num="01">Summary</h2>
  <p>The short version:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>14-day money-back guarantee</strong> on your first purchase of any ZafTech SaaS product.</li>
    <li><strong>Annual plans</strong>: pro-rated refund if you cancel within the first 30 days; after that, cancellation ends renewal but no refund.</li>
    <li><strong>Monthly plans</strong>: no refund after the current billing period starts, but cancellation takes effect at the end of the period.</li>
    <li><strong>Agency services</strong>: governed by the signed Statement of Work, not this policy.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="general" data-num="02">General policy</h2>
  <p>
    If you are unhappy with a ZafTech SaaS product within 14 days of your first payment,
    email <a href="mailto:contact@zaftech.co">contact@zaftech.co</a> and we will refund
    you in full, no questions asked, subject to the per-product rules below. The 14-day
    window applies to first purchase only, not to renewals.
  </p>
  <p>
    After the 14-day window:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Monthly plans are non-refundable for the current billing period. You can cancel to stop future renewals.</li>
    <li>Annual plans are pro-rated to the nearest full month if cancelled within the first 30 days of that annual term, and non-refundable thereafter.</li>
    <li>Automatic renewal charges are refundable within 14 days of the renewal date if the account shows no significant usage in the renewed period.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="per-product" data-num="03">Per-product rules</h2>
  <h3>Convia</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>14-day full refund on first purchase if fewer than 50 form responses have been collected across your account.</li>
    <li>Annual-plan pro-rated refund within first 30 days.</li>
    <li>Add-on credits (extra responses, custom domains) are non-refundable once consumed.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Mizan</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>14-day full refund on first subscription.</li>
    <li>Annual-plan pro-rated refund within first 30 days.</li>
    <li>One-time purchases (custom meal plans, coach packages) follow the per-offer refund rules shown at checkout.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>RMS</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Monthly subscription pro-rated refund within first 30 days of your first subscription; full refund if no transactions have been processed.</li>
    <li>Setup and onboarding fees are non-refundable once onboarding has begun. If we have not yet started onboarding, a full refund is available.</li>
    <li>Hardware, printed materials, and custom integration fees are non-refundable unless the item is defective on arrival.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Anchor</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>14-day full refund on first purchase.</li>
    <li>Usage-based charges (API calls, indexed document volume) beyond the included allowance are non-refundable.</li>
    <li>Custom integration, training, and consulting fees are non-refundable once work has started.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Talos</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>14-day full refund on first purchase.</li>
    <li>Compute charges for executed sandboxes beyond the included allowance are non-refundable.</li>
    <li>Custom integration fees follow the Anchor rule.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="agency" data-num="04">Agency engagements</h2>
  <p>
    Custom engineering engagements, including discovery, design, development, and support
    retainers, are governed by the <strong>Statement of Work (SoW)</strong> signed for
    that engagement. The SoW sets out the payment schedule, deliverables, and any
    refund, clawback, or cancellation terms. This Refund Policy does <em>not</em> apply
    to agency engagements.
  </p>

  <h2 id="how-to-request" data-num="05">How to request a refund</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Email <a href="mailto:contact@zaftech.co">contact@zaftech.co</a> from the email address on your account.</li>
    <li>Include the product name, the order or invoice ID from your Paddle receipt, and a short reason.</li>
    <li>We respond within 2 business days with a decision. If it helps, we may also suggest a downgrade, pause, or credit instead.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 id="processing" data-num="06">Processing time</h2>
  <p>
    Approved refunds are processed by Paddle (our Merchant of Record) to the original
    payment method. Most refunds arrive within 5 to 10 business days; the timing
    ultimately depends on your card issuer or bank.
  </p>

  <h2 id="exceptions" data-num="07">Exceptions</h2>
  <p>
    We reserve the right to deny refunds in cases of:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Repeat refund requests on the same product by the same user.</li>
    <li>Accounts that have violated the <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a> or <a href="/acceptable-use">Acceptable Use Policy</a>.</li>
    <li>Suspected fraudulent, abusive, or automated signup activity.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="disputes" data-num="08">Disputes</h2>
  <p>
    If you disagree with a refund decision, reply to our email and ask for escalation.
    Most issues are resolved this way. You also have the right to raise the matter with
    Paddle as the Merchant of Record, and, where applicable, your card issuer. Please
    talk to us first; we are small and responsive.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
